This is how the conversation went with the clients.

248
00:16:59,703 --> 00:17:01,825
The first idea that they presented to me is they said,

249
00:17:01,885 --> 00:17:04,227
we really liked the movie The Right Stuff.

250
00:17:04,728 --> 00:17:05,448
It's a film from 1983.

251
00:17:05,488 --> 00:17:08,111
Have you guys watched The Right Stuff?

252
00:17:08,151 --> 00:17:08,631
Raise your hands.

253
00:17:09,292 --> 00:17:12,314
So it's like one of these iconic movies about cosmonauts.

254
00:17:12,975 --> 00:17:15,897
It's scored by Bill Conti with a very traditional score,

255
00:17:16,158 --> 00:17:18,440
totally orchestral and beautiful, melodic,

256
00:17:18,760 --> 00:17:20,582
almost like Bach, almost like classical music.

257
00:17:21,642 --> 00:17:25,924
and they did not want choir. This was one of their requirements.

258
00:17:26,584 --> 00:17:30,666
Now I thought to myself, well, that score is awesome, but it was composed in 1983.

259
00:17:31,446 --> 00:17:38,708
So now how do I sort of turn their idea around and still make them feel as if they're giving me the idea,

260
00:17:38,748 --> 00:17:41,149
but like kind of put my ideas like in their brain.

261
00:17:41,609 --> 00:17:45,371
So what I suggest, that's a very important skill for composers to have, to kind of...

262
00:17:46,111 --> 00:17:48,333
share ideas and be really open, be really respectful,

263
00:17:48,373 --> 00:17:50,695
but also present ideas and make your collaborators

264
00:17:50,735 --> 00:17:52,097
think that they came up with the idea.

265
00:17:52,517 --> 00:17:54,879
So I said, how about we approach this entire score.

266
00:17:56,133 --> 00:17:58,114
and make it modern and timeless.

267
00:17:58,515 --> 00:18:01,136
So the timeless component is going to be the classical music,

268
00:18:01,396 --> 00:18:05,359
classical big strings and horn tunes and melodies

269
00:18:05,979 --> 00:18:08,781
and classical chord progressions, almost like Bach.

270
00:18:09,141 --> 00:18:10,482
So we have that classical component,

271
00:18:10,522 --> 00:18:13,003
which is our timeless component.

272
00:18:13,384 --> 00:18:15,905
But as far as the modern sound is concerned,

273
00:18:15,945 --> 00:18:18,967
I mean, all of us have grown basically listening

274
00:18:18,987 --> 00:18:22,289
to these very modern, pulsing, electronic percussive scores.

275
00:18:22,429 --> 00:18:23,770
So I felt compelled to.

276
00:18:24,310 --> 00:18:28,193
have very strong percussion arrangement and synths.

277
00:18:28,514 --> 00:18:30,916
So that's how I combined the traditional melodic themes

278
00:18:31,036 --> 00:18:34,598
for the heroes and orchestra with very modern arrangement

279
00:18:34,618 --> 00:18:35,819
with busy percussion and synths.

280
00:18:36,160 --> 00:18:37,561
And it worked beautifully.

281
00:18:38,529 --> 00:18:43,353
So that's how I sort of turned their idea around and added my own input.

282
00:18:43,413 --> 00:18:45,375
And they totally went, I mean, they just really loved the music.

283
00:18:45,715 --> 00:18:46,396
They went with the idea.

284
