00:27:23,244 --> 00:27:25,565
Hi, I have a question about discussing budget

429
00:27:25,645 --> 00:27:26,886
with developers, like, you know,

430
00:27:27,026 --> 00:27:29,027
if you get even just one live musician,

431
00:27:29,067 --> 00:27:30,808
it can help supplement the sample libraries.

432
00:27:30,848 --> 00:27:31,908
And I was wondering if you have any tips

433
00:27:31,968 --> 00:27:34,029
on how to kind of communicate with developers

434
00:27:34,089 --> 00:27:36,510
about recording budgets or anything relating to that.

435
00:27:37,328 --> 00:27:38,289
That's a really good question.

436
00:27:40,190 --> 00:27:42,731
Most of my games are, I mean, this is purely samples.

437
00:27:42,871 --> 00:27:46,453
But I always make a case, if there's like one musician,

438
00:27:47,154 --> 00:27:50,315
for instance, this is just a wild example, electric cello

439
00:27:50,375 --> 00:27:52,857
that can add so much texture and variety.

440
00:27:53,037 --> 00:27:55,938
And the cello seems to be such a magical instrument

441
00:27:55,998 --> 00:27:57,119
for media scoring.

442
00:27:58,900 --> 00:27:59,860
It's all conversations.

443
00:27:59,960 --> 00:28:03,742
It's all trying to sell the idea that even a small, tiny budget

444
00:28:04,540 --> 00:28:08,024
by adding one instrument can add so much artistic value.

445
00:28:08,184 --> 00:28:11,927
And it's a conversation that you have to have.

446
00:28:11,987 --> 00:28:14,169
But I would say, try to start small.

447
00:28:14,209 --> 00:28:17,172
You can't really say, oh, we have a small mobile game.

448
00:28:17,212 --> 00:28:18,533
I'm going to record orchestra.

449
00:28:18,553 --> 00:28:19,634
Because they're not going to need that.

450
00:28:19,714 --> 00:28:21,055
And they won't be able to afford.

451
00:28:21,555 --> 00:28:24,356
but basically suggest how about we have one very versatile instrument,

452
00:28:24,416 --> 00:28:26,017
maybe a wind instrument or a plucked,

453
00:28:26,517 --> 00:28:28,197
plucked instruments also work really well,

454
00:28:28,317 --> 00:28:29,357
or maybe electric cello,

455
00:28:29,717 --> 00:28:30,958
and then work with one musician,

456
00:28:31,138 --> 00:28:33,598
or maybe work with three musicians, or four.

457
00:28:34,359 --> 00:28:35,439
This is something you can afford,

458
00:28:35,999 --> 00:28:39,640
and it's a small part of the budget, but adds so much.

459
00:28:39,680 --> 00:28:42,201
So the whole idea is that you're going to spend a little bit of money

460
00:28:42,301 --> 00:28:44,961
and get so much more on your return of investment.

461
00:28:45,441 --> 00:28:46,362
That's how I would approach it.

462
00:28:46,402 --> 00:28:48,182
That's how I've always approached it for all these years.

463
00:28:48,662 --> 00:28:51,244
that I worked, I still work with a lot of independent games

464
00:28:51,284 --> 00:28:52,765
and mobile games and indie films,

465
00:28:53,305 --> 00:28:54,446
and the pitch is always the same.

466
00:28:54,526 --> 00:28:56,187
Let's just spend a little bit of money

467
00:28:56,327 --> 00:28:58,629
and get fantastic live cello player.

468
00:28:58,649 --> 00:29:01,230
I just did it on my horror film with a very low budget.

469
00:29:02,071 --> 00:29:04,572
So the idea is you spend a little bit of money

470
00:29:04,672 --> 00:29:05,973
to get huge result.

